---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Experience — Fernando Delgado" bodyClass="collection-type-page">

  <!-- Centered H2 heading -->
  <div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html">
    <div class="sqs-block-content">
      <div class="sqs-html-content">
        <h2 style="text-align:center;">Experience</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Experience header image (~48.57% aspect ratio, 840x409) -->
  <div class="sqs-block image-block">
    <div class="image-block-outer-wrapper">
      <figure class="sqs-block-image-figure intrinsic">
        <div class="image-block-wrapper">
          <div style="height:320px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:8px;">
            <img
              src="/images/experience-header.jpg"
              alt="Photo courtesy of unsplash"
              loading="lazy"
              style="display:block;object-fit:cover;width:100%;height:100%;object-position:50% 50%;"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
          <div class="image-caption"><p>Photo courtesy of unsplash - <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/5Qwz2KyfIBE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://unsplash.com/photos/5Qwz2KyfIBE</a></p></div>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Experience content -->
  <div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html">
    <div class="sqs-block-content">
      <div class="sqs-html-content">

        <h2>Techito</h2>
        <p><strong>Co-Founder &amp; CEO</strong><br />
        <em>2023 – present | Colorado</em><br />
        Fernando co-founded Techito to reimagine hospitality through operational excellence and AI-powered automation. The company became the #1 rated Airbnb co-hosting service in the Denver/Boulder region (4.99 stars) and pioneered immersive stay concepts, including the Soundtrack Hotel.</p>

        <h2>Google &amp; YouTube</h2>
        <p><strong>Group Product Manager</strong><br />
        <em>2018 – 2023 | Mountain View, CA</em><br />
        At Google One, Fernando led a cross-functional org of 100+ to launch Backup by Google One, a feature now active on 2B+ Android devices. He scaled Google's mobile storage business from $50M to $1B+ in annual recurring revenue by driving strategic integrations with Google Photos, Gmail, Drive, and Android.</p>

        <p>At YouTube, he defined and evangelized the product strategy for YouTube Courses, leading a team focused on accelerating structured learning and educational content on the platform.</p>

        <p>Notable achievements include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>Launching Google's consumer VPN and Dark Web monitoring for added member value</p></li>
          <li><p>Driving user clarity through the launch of Storage Manager for Google One</p></li>
          <li><p>Prioritizing privacy-forward design across all initiatives</p></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Yahoo</h2>
        <p><strong>Senior Director, Product Management</strong><br />
        <em>2012 – 2015 | Sunnyvale, CA</em><br />
        At Yahoo, Fernando led mobile product for Yahoo Mail and the homepage app, scaling the mobile user base to 50M+ monthly active users and reaching top rankings in the App Store. He also founded Yahoo's Associate Product Manager program, mentoring over 23 future product leaders who now work across top companies including Stripe, Waymo, Apple, and Uber.</p>

        <h2>Entrepreneur &amp; Product Coach</h2>
        <p><strong>Product Consultant, Founder</strong><br />
        <em>2015 – 2018 | Miami, FL</em><br />
        Fernando launched La Tienda Venezolana, a bootstrapped e-commerce store serving 1M+ visitors with over 1,000 SKUs. In parallel, he coached 50+ aspiring PMs through interview preparation and career development - many of whom went on to land offers at top-tier tech companies including Google, Facebook, and Tesla.</p>

        <h2>Google</h2>
        <p><strong>Product Manager (APM Program Graduate)</strong><br />
        <em>2007 – 2012 | Zurich, Switzerland &amp; Mountain View, CA</em><br />
        Fernando began his career as an APM at Google, contributing to core products including Web Search, Maps, Android Market, Voice Search, and Google+. His contributions included:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>Launching Voice Search for google.com and Android</p></li>
          <li><p>Expanding Google Play to over 100 countries with new billing systems and subscriptions</p></li>
          <li><p>Leading the migration of Panoramio to Google infrastructure</p></li>
          <li><p>Organizing the largest Latin American webmaster conference: Search Masters 2008</p></li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Academic Achievements -->
  <div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html">
    <div class="sqs-block-content">
      <div class="sqs-html-content">
        <h2>Academic Achievements &amp; Distinctions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><p>Putnam Mathematical Competition (2004):<br />
          Ranked <strong>38th nationally</strong> and <strong>1st in Michigan</strong> in the most prestigious individual math competition for undergraduates in North America</p></li>
          <li><p>ACM International Collegiate Programming Contest (2007):<br />
          Ranked <strong>1st in Michigan</strong> in the world's most competitive team-based programming competition</p></li>
          <li><p>University of Michigan, Ann Arbor:<br />
          Graduated with a B.S. in Computer Science and a B.S. in Mathematics (Honors)</p></li>
          <li><p>Telluride House Scholar (2005–2007):<br />
          Selected for a highly competitive scholarship and residential program emphasizing academic excellence, self-governance, and community leadership</p></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Press coverage heading -->
  <div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html">
    <div class="sqs-block-content">
      <div class="sqs-html-content">
        <h2>Press coverage</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

